<TEXT>
colombias cali cocaine cartel is more 
efficient than its more wellknown medellin counterpart and as a 
result it may be shipping more drugs to the united states 
according to a senate report today 
the report by the senate permanent subcommittee on 
investigations minority staff says us law enforcement agencies 
agree the cali cartel although smaller in number runs a much 
more businesslike less highprofile operation than the medellin 
cartel 
medellin appears to be more loosely organized informal and 
spontaneous in its operational style than cali the report says 
in fact some law enforcement officials believe cali actually 
ships more cocaine to the united states than medellin 
mary vincent who presented the report said there are estimates 
that the medellin cartel has as many as 100000 members and the 
cali cartel from 2500 to 6000 members 
bruce m carnes a top aide to national drug control policy 
director william bennett told the subcommittee that the enemy is 
the organizations that produce cocaine and other dangerous drugs 
transport it to our shores distribute it to retailers and users 
throughout america and launder the profits and return them to the 
organizations coffers 
the objective of the war on drugs he said is to put these 
organizations out of business dismantle them 
under questioning by subcommittee chairman sam nunn dga 
carnes acknowedged that the two primary measures of drug abuse in 
the united states the household survey by the national institute on 
drug abuse and a high school survey are not comprehensive 
the household survey does not measure use by students in dorms or 
people in institutions and the survey of high school seniors does 
not take into account those young people who have dropped out of 
school 
so basically what youre saying is after 20 years of fighting 
the socalled war against drugs thats been declared by at least 
four to five presidents of both political partieswe still not 
only dont have adequate tools and we arent using the tools in the 
right direction and the ones we are using to measure our success or 
