cartels dominate the cocaine trade in the western hemisphere it 
notes secondary trafficking groups along colombias north coast 
rent a variety of their smuggling services to the top two and 
conduct their own trafficking operations 
larger drug trafficking organizations are run like corporations 
with each stage of the cocaine processing and distribution handled 
by a separate department the report says 
we found definite indications that a trafficker of the stature 
of medellin cartel leader jose gonzalo rodriguez gacha for 
example will have his own coca paste suppliers his own 
laboratories his own stash sites and his own warehouses in the 
united states the report says 
the report resulting from a yearlong investigation does not 
attempt to determine how the organizations may have been changed or 
disrupted by the crackdown imposed by colombian president virgilio 
barco 
