outside passau said many of the emigres who had cars arrived later 
than expected a lot of them told me they had gone shopping in 
vienna and took in the sights before going on to west germany 
he said 
about 60000 east germans were reported in hungary on sunday 
most of them on vacation but an interior ministry official in 
budapest said monday that 26000 of them had returned home 
