injure or kill someone with a firearm that was not safely stored 
we require childproof caps on aspirin bottles yet we allow 
loaded guns to be left in the kids playroom said rep david 
clarenbach this bill is a small step toward sanity and a giant 
leap for safety 
the measure would set maximum penalties of two years in prison 
and 10000 fines for adults who leave loaded guns or weapons 
accessible to children under 16 resulting in an injury or death 
the bill endorsed by the wisconsin arm of the national rifle 
association and handgun control inc was touted as an effort to 
reduce childhood injuries through education 
this is not a gun control bill its a gun safety bill 
clarenbach said 
he and sen john plewa said the measure was in response to a 
number of accidental shootings involving children this summer in 
madison and milwaukee 
ir would require the department of natural resources to expand 
its hunter safety program to promote gun safety public awareness 
and safe use and storage of weapons the bill also would require gun 
retailers to post information about the penalties for failing to 
secure loaded firearms 
