that flag desecration be prohibited he said is it too much to 
ask those who consider themselves americans to be required to have 
respect for our flag 
the house bill includes a provision for expedited review of the 
law by the supreme court if its constitutionality is challenged and 
an exception so that veterans groups could continue their practice 
of disposal of old wornout flags by burning them 
opponents of the statute said the disposal exception was a 
loophole that could protect unsavory flag burners that they could 
dirty their flags before burning them the bills drafters however 
said the dirtying itself would be illegal 
