national security adviser brent scowcroft during which bush and 
vice president dan quayle dropped by fitzwater said 
defending a white house decision to bar the media and to limit 
yeltsins time with the president fitzwater said we dont want to 
do anything to foster internal conflict that might be associated 
with this trip 
we view him as one of the first elected representatives in the 
soviet union an important spokesman for his point of view 
fitzwater said about yeltsin 
yeltsin a critic of gorbachev has emerged as the leader of a 
small but vocal group of reformers within the newly constituted 
soviet parliament 
the group which includes nobel prize winner andrei d sakharov 
has stopped short of illegally forming a separate party or a 
splinter group within the communist party but is widely viewed as an 
opposition movement 
perestroika should not have been conducted on such a broad 
front we should have concentrated ourselves on such things as 
consumer goods and food yeltsin said in baltimore arguing that 
would have improved soviet life and won greater support 
