a jury was chosen tuesday in the 
cocaine conspiracy trial of five americans accused of helping 
colombian drug lord carlos lehder rivas create one of the first 
largescale smuggling rings 
us district judge john h moore ii scheduled opening arguments 
for wednesday morning 
the panel was selected late tuesday afternoon following two days 
of questioning prospective jurors about what they of lehders trial 
which spanned nearly eight months in 1987 and 1988 
the five charged are accused of working with lehder and others 
from 1974 through 1989 in a conspiracy to distribute cocaine three 
of the men also face importation charges 
lehder 40 who prosecutors said was an architect of the medellin 
cartel was extradited from colombia in 1987 he was convicted in 
may 1988 of smuggling more than 20 tons of cocaine into the united 
states during the late 1970s and early 1980s and sentenced to life 
in prison without parole 
the medellin cartel named for the colombian city where it is 
based is considered the worlds largest illegal cocaine operation 
and is believed to supply 80 percent of the cocaine sold in the 
united states 
many of the bestknown leaders of colombian cocaine cartels were 
indicted in this case dubbed son of lehder by prosecutors but 
remain at large 
on trial are jack carlton reed 58 who was convicted with lehder 
on one conspiracy count and sentenced to 15 years in prison thomas 
howard herington 35 of mill valley calif attorney and pilot 
barry kane 52 of hyannis mass and fort lauderdale donald 
kenneth lady 41 of pomona calif and samuel thomas stewart 53 
of anaheim calif 
their indictment alledges a series of specific acts prosecutors 
say reed often acted as an intermediary between lehder and a corps 
of americans he had working as pilots and distributors kane an 
attorney and pilot is accused of flying cocaine from cartel kingpin 
pablo escobars ranches in colombia to the united states in 1977 
herington is accused of hauling cocaine from florida to 
california in a rented lear jet stewart is accused of helping 
lehder acquire an aircraft and of flying to colombia to pick up 
cocaine and lady is accused of delivering money to be used to build 
an underground cocaine storage facility on the nevadaarizona border 
and of leasing ranches in mexico as cocaine waystations on flights 
from colombia to arizona 
others indicted in the same case but not in custody for trial 
include cartel leaders pablo escobar gaviria jose gonzalo rodriquez 
gacha jorge ochoa vasquez and fabio ochoa vasquez they are on the 
list of the governments mostwanted colombian drug kingpins and 
have remained at large despite a crackdown on the traffickers in 
colombia 
also indicted but not in custody were are financier robert vesco 
who lives in cuba and everette bannister an associate of bahamian 
prime minister lynden o pindling us officials have 
unsuccessfully sought bannisters extradition 
reed is charged with conspiracy to distribute five kilograms or 
more of cocaine and operating a continuing criminal enterprise 
herington is charged with one count of conspiracy to distribute five 
kilograms or more of cocaine 
kane lady and stewart also face the conspiracy count and an 
additional charge of conspiracy to import cocaine into the united 
states 
if convicted they could get sentences ranging from 10 years to 
life 
