a random sampling of catholic students in grades 3 7 and 11 with 
national assessment of educational progress scores of public school 
students in those grades 
average reading ability of catholic students was 58 percent 
better than public school students in grade 3 99 percent better in 
grade 7 and 79 percent better in grade 11 the report said 
