<TEXT>
vietnams military retreat from 
cambodia should hasten the decline in soviet influence in indochina 
and possibly open the door to the west for the first time since 
1975 diplomats in phnom penh say 
vietnams promised pullout of its last 26000 soldiers by sept 
26 will meet part of the price the noncommunist world has long 
demanded for normal ties with indochina vietnam cambodia and laos 
the vietnamese pullout will not meet two key western demands 
that the withdrawal be internationally monitored and that it be part 
of an overall political settlement of the conflict among cambodian 
factions 
diplomats said they expect to see gradual increases in private 
and lowerlevel official contacts and commercial dealings that 
vietnam and cambodia desperately seek with the west 
all around phnom penh are signs that cambodians are looking to a 
future with the west 
english has become the most popular foreign language and an 
entire block is lined with bamboo huts housing englishlanguage 
schools signs that many cambodians foresee a return of the 
americans who roamed their streets during the indochina war 
vietnam and cambodia committed themselves to increased ties with 
the noncommunist world a few years ago when amid economic crises 
they embarked on reforms requiring western trade investment and 
aid they had relied on largely ineffective east bloc aid only 
because the west gave them no other choice said the diplomats who 
spoke only on condition of anonymity 
everyone that wants to come to do business here they are all 
welcome vice prime minister kong samol said in an interview 
in cambodia the opening to the west also is a political 
necessity 
when we speak about the future of this country we have to 
understand one thing that prime minister hun sen and his people 
must change the government to a more capitalistic one because that 
is the only way to be accepted by the international community 
said a frank east bloc diplomat 
phnom penh has been much less committed than the vietnamese 
government in hanoi to socialist doctrine and cambodia could rapidly 
move into the western camp if prince norodom sihanouk the former 
leader who now heads an antigovernment faction returned to a 
position of authority in a political settlement 
the vietnamese are probably fearful that the west would with 
its guilty conscience put everything into cambodia but still 
isolate vietnam said a western aid official 
the strategic value of vietnam and cambodia has declined for the 
soviet union as it recently improved relations with china and no 
longer needs ways to balance its influence in asia but the 
diplomats said cambodia also has become too expensive for president 
mikhail s gorbachevs kremlin 
at the same time they added vietnam and cambodia realized that 
their national security required more balanced relations with the 
superpowers and the association of southeast asian nations the 
areas noncommunist grouping 
vietnam has been moscows closest ally in asia since communist 
forces defeated usbacked indochinese governments in 1975 with 
the prime exception of the united states most western nations 
recognized the new government in hanoi but they imposed economic 
blockades after vietnam invaded cambodia in december 1978 and 
installed a provietnamese communist government 
cambodia has been cut off from the west since the communist khmer 
rouge defeated the usbacked lon nol government in 1975 and 
slaughtered citizens by the hundreds of thousands vietnams 
invasion drove the khmer rouge to the jungles from which they still 
wage a guerrilla war with other antigovernment factions 
in 1987 official cambodian media said the soviet union was 
giving the country 625 million in economic aid for five projects 
for the period 198690 a soviet official said in 1986 that moscow 
was giving 123 billion to 139 billion to vietnam for the same 
period 
moscows most prominent military presence in indochina is at 
vietnams cam ranh bay the former us base that is now considered 
the largest overseas soviet naval base but vietnam said last year 
it may allow other countries to use the base 
an east bloc diplomat said the soviets have withdrawn 60 percent 
of their personnel from cambodia in the past year leaving about 
1000 he said many of those who left were technical experts who 
worked without any result and the soviets decided the resources 
could be better used to resolve their own problems 
for similar reasons moscow also will slash economic aid to 
vietnam it reportedly also has been unhappy with hanois slow 
retreat from cambodia 
the soviets are not very popular said a western ambassador 
in hanoi they dont mix well with the population they failed 
completely to get their confidence many foreigners have married 
vietnamese girls but that is unthinkable for a russian 
cambodia and vietnam were not happy with the soviets limited 
commitment to their development and what they saw as unfair terms of 
aid and trade 
diplomats said some countries including thailand and australia 
may recognize the cambodian government after the vietnamese leave if 
it holds open elections and holds off the guerrillas 
australia was one of the first countries to mediate the cambodian 
issue and has given much aid to cambodia through the united nations 
and nongovernmental organizations 
good relations with phnom penh are crucial to neighboring 
thailands security the government there has said it hopes to see 
indochina change from battlefields to marketplaces 
