drexel pleaded guilty monday to six felonies and began paying 
650 million plus interest and civil insider trading penalties 
closing a major chapter in the 3yearold wall street corruption 
crackdown 
the new york investment firm immediately wrote certified checks 
to three government agencies and a bank that will manage a fund 
earmarked for civil damages claims against drexel 
