<TEXT>
drexel burnham lambert inc has pleaded guilty to 
six felonies and begun paying more than 650 million as punishment 
for unprecedented securities laws violations 
the plea in federal court monday had been expected since drexel 
and the government reached an agreement on the charges in january 
but had been delayed by challenges by drexels indicted bond trader 
michael milken 
drexel pleaded guilty to four counts of securities fraud and two 
counts of mail fraud and agreed to pay a record total of 650 
