<TEXT>
the big three automakers and major oil companies 
say they have held meetings on development of fuels that will 
satisfy president bushs cleanair proposal 
the first meeting was held in july and focused on developing 
fuels that could keep the performance characteristics of gasoline 
while eliminating much of the air pollution caused by 
gasolinepowered engines 
however representatives of general motors corp ford motor co 
and chrysler corp along with the american petroleum institute 
denied a report in mondays automotive news that they had decided to 
try to torpedo efforts to require that methanol be used as the fuel 
of the future 
