talk about future fuels 
this summer bush unveiled a clean air plan that beginning in 
1995 would phase in cars that burn clean fuels such as methanol 
in connecticut and the cities of los angeles houston new york 
milwaukee baltimore philadelphia san diego and chicago where air 
pollution problems are severe 
researchers for the big three the oil and gas industry and 
others have been busy in recent years working on cleanerburning 
