<TEXT>
executives of inland steel industries inc and 
nippon steel corp on tuesday announced plans to spend 450 million 
to build two steelcoating lines at their nearly completed 
jointventure plant in indiana 
the lines called in kote should strengthen inlands position 
as a supplier to the appliance and auto industries primary markets 
for corrosionresistant coated steel products said frank luerssen 
chairman and chief executive of the company at a news conference 
the move will measurably strengthen our joint commitment to 
meet the needs for differentiated steel products in the american 
market luerssen said we now see customers lining up to get 
their share of the materials 
the two production lines will have an annual capacity of 900 
finished tons and will be constructed next to a nearly completed new 
carlisle ind plant where inland and nippon are finishing work on 
a continuous coldrolling mill called in tek 
in tek and inland steels indiana harbor works in east chicago 
ind will provide all the sheet steel for in kote 
the 900 million complex being built at new carlisle ind by 
chicagobased inland and tokyobased nippon is believed to represent 
the largest spending program so far for an americanjapanese joint 
venture in the united states 
it will bring 400 new jobs to the south bend ind area 
the new coating lines will take the coldrolled steel produced at 
the plant and coat it using an electrogalvanizing process or a 
hotdip line 
automakers use galvanized steels highergrade sheets on exposed 
car panels and hotdipped sheets for such things as panels for light 
truck beds 
inland the sixthlargest steel company in the nation supplies 
the three major us carmakers ford chrysler and general motors 
and major japanese auto manufacturers including honda nissan and 
toyota 
nippon is the largest steel maker in the world exporting about 8 
million tons 
hiroshi saito president of nippon said the venture with inland 
represented a joint commitment to japanese carmakers who have built 
us plants and to american companies with a demand for the 
materials 
saito said the new plant will be entirely operational in 1991 
with in tek beginning operations next year 
such ventures he said work to ease tensions about the trade 
imbalance between the united states and japan 
i am confident that this undertaking will play a major symbolic 
role as a constructive attempt to resolve issues between the two 
economies through mutual understanding and cooperation saito said 
in a prepared statement 
nippon and inland will contribute 150 million each to in kote 
with the rest sponsored by debtfinancing inland is assuming 60 
percent of the construction costs for in tek also a joint venture 
inland this year has experienced three consecutive quarterly 
declines blamed partly on seasonal softness in orders but luerssen 
predicted a small gain for the companys fourth quarter 
